    if len(items) <= 1:
        return items

    mid = len(items) // 2
    left = merge_sort(items[:mid], key)
    right = merge_sort(items[mid:], key)

    merged = []
    i = j = 0
    while i < len(left) and j < len(right):
        if key(left[i]) <= key(right[j]):
            merged.append(left[i])
            i += 1
        else:

        if filters else data
    )
